description: COBRA's latest experiment terrorizes the Dreadnok compound in Chicago, but when its path of destruction spreads out into the city streets, G.I.JOE intervenes. However, COBRA is not about to let them go home with their new technological wonder.
name: Malfunction! 2 of 4

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Everything comes to a head, and it's Action Action Action! It's hard enough for G.I.JOE to stop the renegade Battle Android Trooper (BAT), but will the DREADNOKS and the ALLEY VIPERS be too much for our favorite task force to handle? Of course not, but it'll be fun to watch them take the bad guys out.
name: Malfunction! 3 of 4

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: "He's one of the most dangerous men alive. Feared by members of G.I. Joe and Cobra alike, he hasn't been seen in years. This December marks the return of the enigmatic saboteur known as FIREFLY. But whose side is he on?"
name: Malfunction! 4 of 4

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Rock N Roll reunites with former G.I. Joe teammates, Mutt with Junkyard, Alpine, and Bazooka in the small town of Delhi Hills. Expecting a quiet weekend of rest and relaxation, they soon discover that the local tavern they are visiting is actually an underground meeting hall for Cobra sleeper agents.
name: Homecoming 1 of 2

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Rock N Roll reunites with former G.I. Joe teammates, Mutt with Junkyard, Alpine, and Bazooka in the small town of Delhi Hills. Little did they know that the town was filled with Cobra sleeper agents, and the four soon found themselves in the middle of an explosive situation. After a harrowing escape and the arrival of G.I. Joe reinforcements, the group discovered that all evidence of the Cobra front had disappeared...
name: Homecoming 2 of 2

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Cover Girl, Spirit and Snake Eyes investigate a series of child disappearances with strange similarities.  The team finds the missing children, but are unable to rescue them due to mysterious circumstances.  The three G.I. Joe agents return to the newly reformed PIT with an eerie feeling they will encounter the children again...
name: The Family

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: An international coalition of criminals and mercenaries kidnap Flint and Baroness in and effort to discover the whereabouts of the elusive Cobra Commander.  G.I. Joe joins forces with Destro's forces to rescue the missing agents  Aided by former October Guard members, Daina and Lieutenant Gorky, the alliance takes them to the Czech Republic.  However there is a traitor among them...
name: The Cabal Part 1

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description:
In the Bayou of Louisiana a pack of werewolves stalks their prey.  Carnifex, a member of the hunting party, decides he doesn't like the social structure and challenges the Alpha male, resulting in being cast out of the pack.
On his own, he happens upon Desiree, paying respects at her mother's grave. He learns about the Loup-Garou festival taking place that evening.  In werewolf form Carnifex crashes the festival, killing attendees and condemning Desiree to the world of the "Dream Wolves."
name: Night Cry

description: After being attacked and turned by the werewolf Carnifex, Desiree is found unconscious in the woods by a hunter and taken to a hospital for treatment.  Meanwhile, Carnifex looks in town for human food, inadvertently attacking a vampire.  He loses the ensuing fight, and as the vampire begins to feed Desiree undergoes her first transformation.
name: Cries in the Night

description: Desiree experiences her first night in the woods as she begins to change, amazed by the enhanced senses and hunger.  Meanwhile, Carnifex wakes after being fed on by a vampire, feeling strange after-effects and deciding to rest.  This issue is devoted to following Desiree as she comes to the unhappy conclusion that her transformation is not a bad dream but reality as she completes her transformation.
name: Dark

description: For the first time, Desiree is transformed entirely into a wolf.  Carnifex must accept what he has become following the altercation with a vampire.  Months later, Desiree is holding down a job at a local health food store and has moved in with her friend Wendy.  She is also seeing a psychiatrist in the hope of finding a way to control the transformations.  Unfortunately a demon named Venefica has taken an interest in Wendy and Desiree - resulting in an attack at their home.
name: No Pain, No Gain, Part 1

description: Venefica, a demon has taken Desiree and Wendy to hell.   It turns out that Wendy is pregnant and Venefica desires her fetus.    Desiree, helpless in human form,   is restrained and tortured until she forces herself to transform into a werewolf; thus beginning the fight to rescue herself, Wendy the fetus from the clutches of Venefica and eternity in hell.
name: No Pain, No Gain, Part 2

description: Their house destroyed in the fight with Venefica, Desiree and Wendy move to the French Quarter in New Orleans.  They go about their day-to-day lives, not realizing they are being followed by Carniflex, who is now a vampire.
name: I Walk in Dreams With You pt 1
I Walk in Dreams With You pt 2

description: Kyoko's been scouted for a role in this year's most anticipated drama, a remake of the classic Tsukimori. But shades of the past threaten to stifle the production as Kyoko struggles to get into the character of Mio, a young woman with a severely scarred face. Ms. Iizuka, the actress who played the original Mio, is now playing Kyoko's mother, and has grave doubts about Kyoko's ability to do justice to the role. She demands that Kyoko pass an acting test, and quit the production if she fails!
name: Vol. 10

description: Ren's acting test is about to begin, with his entire future hanging in the balance, and he's managed to make his leading lady Itsumi mad at him. Rather than confront him directly, Itsumi decides to hit him where it hurts. Will she sabotage his test, or will Ren be able to get it together and use his legendary acting ability to lead her through the scene?
name: Vol. 13

description: Vie Ghoul is the new band burning up the charts by stealing Sho's moves, and Kyoko's hopping mad on his behalf. Kyoko's confrontation with Sho about his lack of action doesn't go as well as she hoped--Sho gets violent, and the frontman for Vie Ghoul gets a good look at Kyoko's demons. And both men seem a little more interested in Kyoko than Ren would like...
name: Vol. 14

description: Sho decides to take the high road rather than confront Vie Ghoul about their theft of his song. but VG frontman Reino doesn't take kindly to being ignored and devises a devious plan to get Sho's attention--he's going after Kyoko! Normally, Kyoko's not the type of girl that needs rescuing. But for some reason, Reino's presence petrifies her. Will Reino's evil scheme work better than anyone imagined?
name: Vol. 15

description: Saving Kyoko from Reino's attack has finally knocked some sense into Sho's head, and he realizes how much he cares for her. But before he can declare his devotion, Ren shows up to ruin the moment. Both men realize that Kyoko has no idea of their true feelings for her and begin a secret battle for her affections!
name: Vol. 16

description: Dark Moon is getting excellent ratings, and Kyoko is getting tons of offers for more acting jobs! But all the offers are for twisted, damaged characters like Mio. Kyoko doesn't want to get stuck as a character actor, and she certainly doesn't want to play freaks for the rest of her career. But if she refuses all these jobs, will she even have a career left?!
name: Vol. 17

description: Kyoko hasn't had a Love Me Section job in a while, and this newest assignment is pushing her limits. She's now the personal assistant to Koo Hizuri, a Japanese actor turned Hollywood star, and everyone knows how assistants are treated in Hollywood! Can Kyoko see past Koo's meanness, or will his nastiness just make her demons worse?!
name: Vol. 18

description: Koo and Lory can't stop meddling in Kyoko's and Ren's lives. Because while Koo is impressed with Kyoko's talent, he knows that she will never be a great actress unless she can overcome her fatal weakness. And Lory knows that Ren's acting is likewise affected by his refusal to face his past. Can the two old-timers give their young protégés a much-needed kick in the pants, or will their plans blow up in their faces?!
name: Vol. 19

description: It's the season of giving in Tokyo, but Lory's granddaughter Maria is in no mood to celebrate. Kyoko, never one to sit out a challenge, finally gets Maria to admit what has her so soured on the holidays. It turns out December 24 is Maria's birthday--and the anniversary of her mother's death! Can Kyoko work a Christmas miracle and give this little girl a happy birthday?
name: Vol. 20

description: Kyoko is basking in the glow of working a Christmas miracle and getting some birthday booty of her own. But she's so unused to this kind of joy that she ends up late to the script reading for her new drama. Now her whole day is a mess and Ren is mad at her! Can Kyoko balance revenge, a career and her own happiness?
name: Vol. 21

description: Discovering that different Fractals possess different qualities, the SQUADDIES are stunned when one falls nearby and imbues them with the power of...overweightedness! How long will it take them to save the day when they've all been supersized...?!Also, the Falcon takes us on "A Tour of the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier!" and Wolverine is forced to take Reptil and Falcon on a "Camping Trip!"
name: 2-Ton Squaddies / A Tour of the S.H.I.E.L.D Hellcarrier! / Wolverine, Falcon, and Reptil in the Camping Trip!

description: Things heat up in this island adventure, the penultimate installment of Tails' exotic voyage! With Antoine's ultimate fate revealed, Tails and Bunnie leap into action. As they prepare for an all-out assault on the Battle Bird Armada, the villains are setting their final trap. Will the brave duo foil the fiendish plot?
name: Trouble in Paradise, Part Three

description: The centerpiece of Marvel's 70th Anniversary celebration! Who is the mysterious old man who lies on his deathbed in a hospital in 1939, and how does his passing mark the beginning of the first heroic age of the Marvel Universe - and signal the rise of the superhumans? Ed Brubaker and Steve Epting unveil the defining story of the origin of the Marvel Universe, revealing the hidden connections that unite the earliest costumed champions, and whose reverberations are felt dramatically into the present day! It's a world on the brink of war, and the race is on to create the world's first super-soldier! Witness the first days of the Human Torch, the Sub-Mariner and many more - how they shaped the world to come, and how the future they would create in turn shaped them! The must-read event of the season for any Marvel fan from the Award-Winning creators who redefined Captain America for the modern audience! Collecting THE MARVELS PROJECT #1-8.
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: The Marvels Project: Birth of the Super Heroes

description: This issue was the second of a six week "summer of fun". A running thread through these six issues was Minnie the Minx's attempts to become famous. As such, several celebrities appear in Minnie's stories this week.

name: Dave Berg Looks at Modern Thinking

volume.name: Mad's Dave Berg Looks at Modern Thinking

description:
1. Stuffed Scarecrow  Farmer (Al Falfa) 
 
 2. Jungle of the Unknown (Mighty Mouse)
 
3. The Nuisance  (Heckle and Jeckle) 
  
4.  An Honest Mistake (Dimwit)
 
5. Tracer of Lost Persons (Gandy Goose)  
 
6. The Big Contest (Mighty Mouse)  
 
7. No Sale (Dimwit)  
 
8. Paul Terry's Terry Bears
name: Jungle of the Unknown

description: The GI Joes aren't just sworn to protect, they were born to protect. They are a supreme strike force who will go where others fear, fight where others fall, and triumph where all others have failed. So what's happened! Could it be that the GI Joes have been tried and convicted for criminal acts against InterAlliance? How has this force for good been so thoroughly corrupted?
name: Red Scream Part 1: Hunted

description: The GI Joes are wanted dead or alive! Hunted for crimes they didn't commit, the 'Joes begin a desperate search to find the foes who framed them. Even as things look bleak for America's greatest fighting force, rumors begin to surface of a legendary 'Joe who vanished in the year 2000. Has this mysterious agent once again emerged from the ashes, and if so, is he the 'Joes' last hope?
name: Red Scream Part 2: Shake Hands With Satan

description: The past collides with the future as the GI Joes' tough-as-nails living legend, Sgt. Savage, enters a virtual-reality simulation of battle-torn World War II Germany! But when the program goes haywire, Savage isn't sure if he's experiencing VR or the real thing! If he dies in the program, he dies in real life, and the only way back to his reality is through an entire army of very real Nazi soldiers!
name: All This and World War II; The Last, Wild Heart Part 1: The Fourth Man

description: NEW DOUBLE-SIZED FORMAT! This new version of America's longest-running magazine of classic comics has twice as many pages of strips as the earlier version, on better paper, and includes 8 pages of full-color comic strips, wrapped in a new cover by Mark Schultz of Cadillacs and Dinosaurs and Prince Valiant. Inside are stories such as Flash Gordon, Tarzan, Modesty Blaise, Steve Canyon, The Phantom, and many more, including the first Mandrake the Magician story from 1934, never before reprinted in English.
name: Flash Gordon

description: Three fantastic crossovers — all written by Warren Ellis — are collected in one spectacular Softcover! This volume collects PLANETARY/THE AUTHORITY, PLANETARY/JLA, and PLANETARY/BATMAN, featuring gorgeous art by fan-favorites John Cassaday, Phil Jimenez and Jerry Ordway!
name: TPB

description: Great jumping on point for new readers, as the book covers the whole first story arc! We have an ALL NEW version of issue #3…all new story and all new art! It’s the story BETWEEN the story! Plus we have the first story arc synopsis to get everyone caught up to speed, and some cool extra "Captain Action Files" pages!

The Jewel of the Sun Goddess has been stolen and if Snake Eyes doesn't recover it, the entire world will suffer the consequences...
(From Back Cover) 
 
Once again Devil's Due blazes a new trail - this time into the manga market! Written to be accessible, loosely based on Classic G.I. Joe continuity, "Tales of the Arashikage" is a black and white graphic novel for all ages! The Arashikage Ninja Clan is the tie that binds Snake-Eyes, Jinx, and Storm Shadow. They are the last of a once-powerful Clan - and now, someone is out to steal one of the last objects of their heritage. A relic of great power, the Jewel of the Sun Goddess had been guarded by the Arashikage for centuries. Now, the mysterious gem could give the ultimate power to the forces of evil-and in doing so, destroy the last remnants of the Clan. Get ready for wall-to-wall Ninja action!

Whet your appetite for Alex Ross, Jim Krueger and Steve Sadowski's 12-part AVENGERS/INVADERS maxi-series with these classic tales! Witness the Invaders' first appearance in AVENGERS #71 (1969), as Earth's Mightiest Heroes encounter the wartime Captain America, Human Torch and Sub-Mariner - and experience the story from the Invaders' point of view in INVADERS ANNUAL #1 (1977). Finally, the Invaders thwart a Nazi assassination attempt on President Roosevelt and Winston Churchill in GIANT-SIZE INVADERS #2 (2005). Also featuring in-depth dossiers on both teams and AVENGERS/INVADERS preview pages!    
 
Reprints "Endgame!" from Avengers #71, "The Wrath of the Reaper!" from Invaders #10, "Okay, Axis -- Here We Come!" from Invaders Annual #1, and "A Drive in the Country" from Giant-Size Invaders #2

volume.name: Devil's Due Free Comic Book Day 2005

description: Military bases, high-tech manufacturing plants and research facilities across America are falling victim to sabotage. The destruction is quick and savage, leaving only a tattered U.S. flag to mark that anything was there in the first place. It will take a special group to cure this disease, a warrior force who will go where others fear, fight where others fall, and triumph where all others have failed. A force known as G I Joe. It's been said that in times of desperation, heroism reveals itself... and never have the times been more desperate!
name: The Hour of the Iron Claw; From the Ashes Part 1

description: Nine unique individuals with amazing courage, exceptional training and superior skills and physical abilities have come together for a dire cause. The world is buckling under the forces of S.K.A.R. (Soldiers of Kaos, Anarchy, and Ruin), and these soldiers of freedom may be our last hope! Ballistic, Black Dragon, Freight, Harpoon, Mayday, Metalhead, Quick Stryke, Sgt. Savage and Lt. Stone - they go where others fear, fight where others fall, and triumph where others fail. They protect the world from the forces of evil under a single, time-honored code-name: GI JOE.
name: Pawn of the Iron Claw; From the Ashes Part 2

description: With its ability to enhance the growth of vegetation, Ferti-Gel may well be the solution to world hunger - it could make famine a thing of the past. But there are some who thrive on the hunger of others, factions who seek profit in every solution. And, fortunately, there are also those who would stand against such evil. Ballistic, Black Dragon, Freight, Harpoon, Mayday, Metalhead, Quick Stryke, Sgt. Savage and Lt. Stone - separately they are unique individuals with superior physical skills, intelligence and the finest military training. Together, they are the vanguard against whatever forces may threaten freedom in the world of the 21st century! Together, they are GI JOE.
name: The Gang's All Here; From the Ashes Part 3

description: Ferti-Gel was the chemical miracle that could have fed the world's hungry millions. But in the hands of The Iron Klaw, it has instead become a weapon of unspeakable terror. The only force that stands between The Iron Klaw and total global domination is a group of determined warriors who go by the name of GI JOE! Also included is the finale of "GI JOE: From the Ashes," chronicling the events of today that have created the GI JOE of tomorrow!
name: The Ultimate Price; From the Ashes Part 4
